docs.lead_paragraph: When Postmaster General James A. Farley .dedicates the new Federal Office Building at Church and Vesey Streets tomorrow morning he will still a clamor heard around lower New York for the last forty yeas and various groups concerned with civic improvement may rest happy, their long struggle virtually ended.

headline.main: A DOWNTOWN ERA TO PASS TOMORROW; Opening of Federal Building in Church St. to Mark End of Old Postoffice Eyesore
